5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 716, L.D. 1834, “An Act to Allow Dental
10 Care Providers to Opt In to Receive Claim Reimbursement Payments Made by Virtual
11 Credit Cards”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Clarify the Availability of Alternative Claims Payment Methods to Dental
14 Care Providers '
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 24-A MRSA §2436, sub-§1-A, as amended by PL 2023, c. 232, §1, is
18 further amended to read:
19 1-A. A claimant, including a health care provider, may submit simultaneously a claim
20 for payment with all carriers potentially liable for payment of the claim whether primary
21 or secondary. Payment or denial of a claim by each carrier must be made within 30 calendar
22 days after the carrier has received all information needed to pay or deny the claim whether
23 or not another carrier with which it is attempting to coordinate has acted on the claim. Upon
24 request by a health care provider, a carrier shall provide the health care provider a method
25 for making a claims payment using an electronic funds transfer through the automated
26 clearinghouse network. Any payment made must be in accordance with rules adopted by
27 the superintendent relative to coordination of benefits. For the purposes of this subsection,
28 "health care provider" includes a person licensed to provide dental care services under Title
29 32, chapter 143, subchapter 3 and "carrier" includes an insurer that provides dental
30 insurance.'
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR1972(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 716, L.D. 1834
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. Under current law, a carrier
33 must provide a health care provider a method for making claims payments using an
44 electronic funds transfer through the automated clearinghouse network. The amendment
55 provides that, for the purposes of that requirement, a health care provider includes a person
66 licensed to provide dental services under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 32, chapter 143,
77 subchapter 3 and a carrier includes an insurer that provides dental insurance.
